01:47.984 --> 01:50.987
(THEME MUSIC)

02:37.075 --> 02:40.495
- (ORCHESTRA TUNES)
- MAN: Places, everyone.

02:42.789 --> 02:44.916
Why aren't you in costume?

02:45.083 --> 02:47.460
OLIVIA: I'm not
in this production.

02:48.711 --> 02:50.713
Paprika's in this first scene.

02:50.880 --> 02:54.259
Paprika? What...
what play is this?

02:54.425 --> 02:56.219
I'm counting you down.

02:58.388 --> 03:01.307
Five, four, three...

03:01.474 --> 03:04.018
(CLICKS)

03:05.937 --> 03:07.647
Miss Godfrey, that was your cue.

03:09.482 --> 03:11.526
(TREMBLES) But I don't
even know how I got here.

03:11.693 --> 03:13.736
Line!

03:13.903 --> 03:17.824
Paprika -"Well, all fanny
and no fact, as usual.

03:17.991 --> 03:19.993
"I suppose Guntar
should tell Uncle Isenglass

03:20.159 --> 03:22.579
"about the poultry accident."

03:23.913 --> 03:26.332
The audience is waiting.

03:26.499 --> 03:28.793
(CLICKS)

03:29.794 --> 03:31.421
Will you stop that?

03:31.588 --> 03:33.464
CHANGO: You've been standing
there making scary faces

03:33.631 --> 03:35.425
and mumbling for
the last five minutes.

03:35.592 --> 03:37.927
Since when is it against
the law to daydream?

03:38.094 --> 03:41.139
I don't think that's what
the doctors call it, honey.

03:41.306 --> 03:43.391
Time's wasting.
We gotta get your new body.

03:43.558 --> 03:46.436
- Bip, bip, bip.
- But I'm getting better.

03:46.603 --> 03:49.522
The borax and green tea paste
is curing me.

03:50.690 --> 03:53.651
It's medically proven
to reverse melanoma.

03:53.818 --> 03:56.154
I...read it somewhere.

03:56.321 --> 03:58.239
Yeah, you look fantastic.

03:58.406 --> 04:01.451
Mmm, those horrible blue lines
are getting fainter every day.

04:01.618 --> 04:03.536
Oops!

04:05.121 --> 04:07.123
Bip, bip, bip!

04:09.876 --> 04:11.920
You know what would
look great on you?

04:12.086 --> 04:15.089
Your big wide-brim hat
and some Jackie O sunglasses.

04:15.256 --> 04:16.882
Oh, good idea.

04:17.050 --> 04:20.345
I should avoid the sun anyway,
especially while I'm healing.

04:24.098 --> 04:27.101
(MAN WHEEZES AND GROANS)

04:30.647 --> 04:32.315
We've been trying to reach you.

04:32.482 --> 04:34.776
I need Pryce. Get Pryce.

04:34.943 --> 04:36.444
It just didn't seem
like the sort

04:36.611 --> 04:38.154
of thing one leaves
on voicemail.

04:38.321 --> 04:41.574
I've been shot, you fucking
idiot. Get me Pryce!

04:42.909 --> 04:45.954
(GROANS)

04:46.955 --> 04:48.873
Dr Pryce is dead.

04:51.209 --> 04:53.628
What?

04:53.795 --> 04:55.880
It happened last night.

04:58.174 --> 05:00.385
- How?
- Um...

05:00.551 --> 05:02.345
One of his patients
had a psychotic break

05:02.512 --> 05:04.514
and went...berserk,

05:04.681 --> 05:08.393
stabbed him, uh...

05:08.559 --> 05:10.186
..severed the abdominal aorta

05:10.353 --> 05:12.480
and he was, um,
gone in a few minutes.

05:12.647 --> 05:14.774
This is fucking not...

05:14.941 --> 05:16.734
This is not happening!

05:16.901 --> 05:18.444
(GROANS)

05:18.611 --> 05:20.279
Wait. Who did this to you?

05:20.446 --> 05:22.198
It doesn't matter.
It doesn't matter.

05:22.365 --> 05:25.201
Just stop...
just stop the bleeding.

05:29.414 --> 05:31.624
No vital organs hit,
but there's a lot of blood.

05:31.791 --> 05:34.043
(ROMAN LAUGHS)

05:37.463 --> 05:39.424
(METAL CLATTERS)

05:45.596 --> 05:47.223
- (BOOTS THUD)
- (ROMAN GASPS)

05:47.390 --> 05:50.893
(GROANS) Fucker!

05:53.563 --> 05:55.106
BLINSKY: OK.

05:55.273 --> 05:57.775
(ROMAN GRUNTS)

06:00.445 --> 06:02.905
Ohh! (EXHALES HEAVILY)

06:06.159 --> 06:08.786
- Ohh...
- Press down.

06:13.458 --> 06:14.959
Arggh! The fuck?

06:15.126 --> 06:18.421
Protamine sulfate.
Intrajugular clotting agent.

06:18.588 --> 06:20.089
Hold still.

06:20.256 --> 06:22.508
(GROANS)

06:22.675 --> 06:24.635
(INHALES SHARPLY)

06:24.802 --> 06:27.597
Ohh... (LAUGHS)

06:44.030 --> 06:47.075
- Hey, Nacho.
- Big sister plankin'.

06:47.241 --> 06:48.868
(CHUCKLES)

06:49.035 --> 06:51.370
- Sorry I bailed.
- You don't gotta apologise.

06:51.537 --> 06:54.040
Everybody bailed on
account of the 5-0.

06:54.207 --> 06:56.709
- How you doin'?
- Doin'.

06:56.876 --> 07:00.254
- You?
- Trying to get paid.

07:00.421 --> 07:04.258
Aluminum's 50 cents a pound.
Copper's four times that.

07:05.259 --> 07:09.555
- Could you...
- What about everybody else?

07:09.722 --> 07:12.016
Everybody else
found another hole.

07:12.183 --> 07:15.561
Good people, free food...
It was too good to last.

07:15.728 --> 07:18.189
I guess so.

07:19.732 --> 07:21.692
You hear from anybody else?

07:25.696 --> 07:27.824
I'm sorry, Shell-bell.

07:27.990 --> 07:30.785
Guys like Aitor,
they don't look back.

07:33.454 --> 07:36.374
So what you trying
to get into next?

07:38.000 --> 07:39.836
I...

07:40.878 --> 07:42.839
..I don't know.

07:57.270 --> 07:59.063
(GRUNTS)

08:03.151 --> 08:05.153
(GROANS)

08:14.871 --> 08:18.291
(SOMBRE MUSIC)

09:15.890 --> 09:17.558
(LOCK CLICKS AND BUZZES)

09:21.187 --> 09:23.481
- Morning.
- Should I go pick up the baby?

09:23.648 --> 09:25.566
She's not here?

09:25.733 --> 09:27.693
Peter took her
to the park yesterday.

09:27.860 --> 09:29.820
I...I assumed
he had her for the night.

09:29.987 --> 09:32.240
- You didn't think to call me?
- I...

09:32.406 --> 09:34.700
Shut the fuck up.

09:36.911 --> 09:38.663
(EXHALES)

09:40.748 --> 09:42.583
Fuck...

09:46.003 --> 09:47.838
(MOBILE PHONE CLICKS)

09:54.971 --> 09:56.847
(PHONE TRILLS)

10:18.244 --> 10:19.954
(PHONE TRILLS)

10:34.677 --> 10:36.304
(PHONE BEEPS)

10:37.471 --> 10:39.932
(CROSSING SIGNAL DINGS)

10:48.149 --> 10:50.276
(EXHALES)

10:55.573 --> 10:57.450
(ENGINE REVS)

11:03.622 --> 11:05.624
(EERIE MUSIC)

11:06.792 --> 11:08.794
(THUNDER CRACKS)

11:11.714 --> 11:14.091
(INHALES SHARPLY)

11:21.849 --> 11:23.642
DESTINY: Now you know
how it feels.

11:25.227 --> 11:26.854
If you were just
straight with me,

11:27.021 --> 11:28.689
none of this would've happened.

11:28.856 --> 11:32.985
You were really fucking stupid,
Peter, but what's done is done.

11:33.152 --> 11:35.654
I'm dead. (CHUCKLES)

11:35.821 --> 11:38.074
And you're as good as.

11:40.159 --> 11:42.036
I'm not even supposed
to be talking to you

11:42.203 --> 11:43.913
until it's official,
but with Roman running around

11:44.080 --> 11:45.748
killing all these people
for no good reason,

11:45.915 --> 11:47.541
you don't really want him

11:47.708 --> 11:49.835
walking away large
and in charge, hmm?

11:50.002 --> 11:53.047
- (MURMURS)
- No. I didn't think so.

11:53.214 --> 11:57.676
But you're running out
of oxygen, so...

11:58.677 --> 12:01.430
Cuz, if you want this
to end differently,

12:01.597 --> 12:05.643
you better pray for a miracle
or dig like a motherfucker.

12:08.896 --> 12:10.898
(SCRAPING)

12:18.155 --> 12:19.782
(GRUNTS)

12:19.949 --> 12:21.992
(WOLF SNARLS)

12:22.159 --> 12:24.036
(WOLVES WHIMPER)

12:29.375 --> 12:31.210
(WOLF SNIFFS)

12:31.377 --> 12:34.380
(GROWLS LOWLY)

12:48.853 --> 12:50.855
(INHALES)

12:51.981 --> 12:53.732
(MOANS LOWLY)

12:54.733 --> 12:56.735
(CROW CAWS IN DISTANCE)

13:01.157 --> 13:03.492
(WINCES)

13:07.496 --> 13:10.666
(GROANS)

13:25.931 --> 13:27.558
Ohh...

13:42.573 --> 13:44.366
(LOCK CLICKS AND BUZZES)

14:24.990 --> 14:26.951
- Hello, Mom.
- (GASPS)

14:28.953 --> 14:31.789
I knew you were here
the second I walked in.

14:31.956 --> 14:33.791
(SNIFFS DEEPLY) It's the smell.

14:33.958 --> 14:35.584
You smell like a corpse.

14:35.751 --> 14:37.586
- (GRUNTS)
- (CLATTERING)

14:38.587 --> 14:41.423
It hurts, right? The tumour's
wrapped around your optic nerve.

14:42.591 --> 14:46.554
(WHISTLES) Come on.
Over here. Come on.

14:46.720 --> 14:48.347
- (GRUNTS)
- (CHUCKLES)

14:48.514 --> 14:50.266
- Ohh!
- (LAUGHS)

14:51.392 --> 14:54.311
Arggh! Ohh!

14:54.478 --> 14:57.147
(WEEPS)

14:57.314 --> 14:59.108
Roman, please help me.

14:59.275 --> 15:02.570
With what? Feeding on me?

15:02.736 --> 15:05.698
Commandeering my body?

15:05.864 --> 15:11.036
Yeah, your good pal Pryce
filled me in before he carked.

15:12.371 --> 15:14.039
I'm dying.

15:14.206 --> 15:17.042
I...I can't think straight.

15:17.209 --> 15:18.961
That's why I need your help.

15:19.128 --> 15:21.255
Why would I ever help you?

15:21.422 --> 15:23.549
(WEEPING) Because you love me.

15:23.716 --> 15:25.509
Despite everything...

15:26.510 --> 15:28.220
..there was a time
when we were close.

15:28.387 --> 15:31.849
'Were'. You took care of that.

15:32.891 --> 15:34.602
You're becoming more like me,

15:34.768 --> 15:36.895
every moment,
in everything you do.

15:39.940 --> 15:43.611
Surely you understand
why I am the way I am.

15:43.777 --> 15:46.822
I mean, I'm just
not someone who can give up.

15:48.616 --> 15:52.286
Maybe we're both creatures
of absolute will.

15:52.453 --> 15:54.788
You can will all you want.

15:54.955 --> 15:57.249
You're already dead

15:57.416 --> 15:59.084
and I'm looking
forward to the part

15:59.251 --> 16:01.253
where you shut the fuck up
permanently.

16:03.088 --> 16:05.049
Help me get Annie.

16:06.300 --> 16:12.222
And I'll just go away.
I'll never bother you again.

16:12.389 --> 16:15.851
Whatever you want.

16:16.852 --> 16:20.773
The only problem with that
is that you aren't dead.

16:20.939 --> 16:23.192
(SCREAMS)

16:25.819 --> 16:29.573
I made you what you are.
I taught you how to survive.

16:31.909 --> 16:33.786
That's why I don't
need you anymore.

16:33.952 --> 16:37.414
No, don't.
You'll always need me.

16:37.581 --> 16:40.292
Yeah? I'm stronger
than you ever were.

16:40.459 --> 16:41.960
No...

16:42.127 --> 16:44.797
- ROMAN: It's time to go.
- No.

16:44.963 --> 16:46.757
Your time is up.

16:46.924 --> 16:48.717
(OLIVIA SOBS)

16:56.016 --> 16:58.435
OLIVIA: I'm not
supposed to be here.

16:58.602 --> 17:00.729
I don't know what to say.

17:00.896 --> 17:02.773
(AUDIENCE MURMURS)

17:04.775 --> 17:07.152
Line?

17:07.319 --> 17:09.154
(SCATTERED LAUGHTER)

17:09.320 --> 17:11.448
MAN: Boo!

17:14.910 --> 17:19.665
- (LAUGHTER GROWS)
- Hell is murky.

17:20.665 --> 17:22.751
Fie, my lord, fie!

17:22.917 --> 17:25.628
A soldier and afeard?

17:27.548 --> 17:29.508
What need we fear who knows it

17:29.675 --> 17:32.302
when none can call
our power to account.

17:32.469 --> 17:34.304
(LAUGHTER CONTINUES)

17:34.471 --> 17:37.433
Yet...who would...

17:37.599 --> 17:40.853
MAN: Speak up, darling! (LAUGHS)

17:41.019 --> 17:42.938
WOMAN: I tell ya,
if I had a tomato...

17:43.105 --> 17:46.150
- Who...
- (LAUGHTER CONTINUES)

17:46.316 --> 17:48.152
Line.

17:50.362 --> 17:52.364
Line!

17:54.199 --> 17:56.952
What is my fucking line?!

17:59.830 --> 18:01.915
(SCREAMS)

18:02.082 --> 18:05.085
Ohh! (WEEPS)

18:07.463 --> 18:09.131
(LOCK CLICKS)

18:09.298 --> 18:12.301
(SOBS)

18:19.349 --> 18:24.354
What am I supposed to do?
Give up?

18:25.397 --> 18:28.025
Don't talk nonsense.

18:40.287 --> 18:43.290
(EERIE MUSIC BOX TUNE)

18:55.302 --> 18:58.305
(INHALES AND EXHALES DEEPLY)

19:01.892 --> 19:04.895
(CAR ENGINE RUMBLES)

19:09.942 --> 19:12.945
(GENTLE GUITAR MUSIC
PLAYS SOFTLY)

19:16.114 --> 19:19.743
- Hey.
- She's been an angel.

19:19.910 --> 19:24.206
I fed and changed her.
Put her down about an hour ago.

19:24.373 --> 19:26.917
Thanks.

19:27.084 --> 19:29.044
And we have a visitor.

19:40.472 --> 19:42.516
(SIGHS)

19:53.402 --> 19:55.863
- (INHALES SHARPLY)
- Sorry.

19:56.029 --> 19:58.490
- It has to be tight.
- Mmm.

20:00.701 --> 20:02.703
You're lucky you're alive.

20:02.870 --> 20:06.039
Let's not tempt fate. Come on.
I'll drive you to the hospital.

20:06.206 --> 20:09.543
No. There's too many people
asking too many questions.

20:09.710 --> 20:12.504
It's better to stay
off the grid.

20:15.048 --> 20:16.967
You don't have to be
doing any of this.

20:18.427 --> 20:20.929
I didn't do enough
when it really counted.

20:21.096 --> 20:23.682
If I had, none of this
would be happening.

20:24.683 --> 20:26.977
You didn't know
what Roman was capable of.

20:27.144 --> 20:28.812
Neither did I.

20:28.979 --> 20:31.732
You did what you could
to stop him.

20:31.899 --> 20:34.026
Let me help.

20:35.569 --> 20:39.615
- We'll go after him together.
- No, this isn't your fight.

20:40.699 --> 20:43.493
The only way to bring Roman down
is for me to turn.

20:45.203 --> 20:47.331
So you'll wait a month,

20:47.497 --> 20:49.583
give you a chance
to get your strength back.

20:49.750 --> 20:52.377
Turning against the moon
exposes you to enormous risk.

20:52.544 --> 20:55.005
You've turned against
the moon before.

20:55.172 --> 20:56.924
This time,
there is no coming back.

20:57.090 --> 21:00.761
You're not the first
of your kind I've run across.

21:03.138 --> 21:05.515
Look what he's done
in three days.

21:05.682 --> 21:07.935
Give him a month,
it'll be hell on earth.

21:08.101 --> 21:09.853
Promise me you'll wait...

21:10.020 --> 21:11.647
(BABY BURBLES)

21:11.813 --> 21:13.607
..for her sake.

21:22.616 --> 21:24.493
PETER: I'm not
in peak form anyway.

21:24.660 --> 21:26.411
I can take care of her.

21:26.578 --> 21:29.206
You need to concentrate
on getting well.

21:29.373 --> 21:32.459
You'll call me when it's over
and I'll bring her back to you.

21:44.805 --> 21:46.431
ANNIE: Where did that come from?

21:46.598 --> 21:49.601
My end of a business deal
I'd just as soon forget.

21:49.768 --> 21:52.104
You two need it more than I do.

21:54.064 --> 21:55.941
PETER: I travel light.

22:01.113 --> 22:02.906
(DOOR SHUTS)

22:45.449 --> 22:48.452
(TENSE MUSIC)

22:56.334 --> 22:58.587
COMPUTERISED VOICE:
<i>You have three new messages.</i>

22:58.754 --> 23:01.423
OLIVIA: <i>Hello, Annie, dear.
It's your mother.</i>

23:01.590 --> 23:04.384
<i>We haven't talked
in a while - my fault.</i>

23:04.551 --> 23:07.262
<i>I've been under the weather.
I...I'd love to see you.</i>

23:07.429 --> 23:09.556
<i>Please come by. I miss you.</i>

23:09.723 --> 23:11.349
COMPUTERISED VOICE:
<i>Next message.</i>

23:11.516 --> 23:15.270
OLIVIA: <i>Me again. I'm calling
to see if you got my message.</i>

23:15.437 --> 23:16.980
<i>I'm around all day.</i>

23:17.147 --> 23:18.690
COMPUTERISED VOICE:
<i>Next message.</i>

23:18.857 --> 23:20.650
OLIVIA: <i>Are you coming by?</i>

23:28.533 --> 23:31.536
(FEARSOME MUSIC)

23:39.252 --> 23:42.255
(MOBILE PHONE RINGS)

23:45.175 --> 23:46.927
(PHONE BEEPS)

23:47.094 --> 23:49.471
ROMAN: This you?

23:49.638 --> 23:51.264
PETER: Yeah.

23:51.431 --> 23:53.558
(ROMAN CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

23:53.725 --> 23:56.103
You sound pretty chipper
for a dead guy.

23:56.269 --> 23:57.896
PETER: Sorry to ruin your day.

23:58.063 --> 24:00.065
Maybe next time, you'll
remember to cut off my head.

24:00.232 --> 24:02.275
ROMAN: Who says there
has to be a next time?

24:02.442 --> 24:04.986
You were the one
who shot me, remember?

24:05.153 --> 24:08.532
I was just defending myself
so I could go home to Nadia.

24:08.698 --> 24:10.492
So Daddy could
kiss her goodnight

24:10.659 --> 24:12.285
reeking of blood
and cheap perfume

24:12.452 --> 24:14.371
from the dead hooker
you left in the alley?

24:14.538 --> 24:18.125
You can hate me all you want,
but you need to ask yourself

24:18.291 --> 24:20.418
what's in everyone's best
interests moving forward.

24:20.585 --> 24:25.006
You and me and Annie -
we all did fucked-up shit.

24:26.007 --> 24:28.552
But if we keep this going,
we're gonna do worse shit.

24:31.221 --> 24:33.932
That's hard to believe.
You set the bar pretty high.

24:34.099 --> 24:35.976
No more killing, Peter.

24:36.977 --> 24:40.397
All you gotta do
is give me my daughter back

24:40.564 --> 24:42.899
and we'll go our separate ways,
I promise.

24:51.074 --> 24:53.660
Nadia would be better off dead
than living with you.

24:53.827 --> 24:56.329
She's my daughter, Peter!

24:56.496 --> 24:58.456
She's Letha's daughter.

25:00.333 --> 25:02.460
I'm trying to give you
a way out of this.

25:02.627 --> 25:05.046
There is no way out.

25:06.298 --> 25:08.758
You murdered Destiny. I can't
let you walk away from that.

25:08.925 --> 25:12.053
You couldn't have bought Andreas
a bus ticket out of town?

25:12.220 --> 25:15.265
You had no other choice
than to rat him out?

25:17.893 --> 25:19.603
Andreas had to die.

25:19.769 --> 25:22.439
ROMAN: Only Destiny tried to
put it all on me at the end

25:22.606 --> 25:24.191
'cause she wouldn't...
she couldn't believe

25:24.357 --> 25:27.027
that you were too gutless
to admit what you did,

25:27.194 --> 25:29.487
that you were that weak,
that you were that pathetic!

25:29.654 --> 25:31.281
Everything that
you hate about Olivia,

25:31.448 --> 25:33.074
that's what you've become.

25:33.241 --> 25:35.660
Norman didn't even want
to admit that you were his son.

25:35.827 --> 25:38.288
And...and Annie, who you
just fucked a couple times,

25:38.455 --> 25:40.415
she wants you dead.

25:40.582 --> 25:42.459
I just came late to the party.

25:43.501 --> 25:45.378
And the model fucking family
you come from.

25:45.545 --> 25:47.881
I mean, your mother couldn't
keep a roof over her head

25:48.048 --> 25:49.674
that wasn't attached
with a guard tower.

25:49.841 --> 25:54.095
And Destiny, she rafted up
with this fucking lowlife

25:54.262 --> 25:56.056
who caused this whole
thing to happen.

25:56.223 --> 26:01.394
All I did was try to keep you
from not going down too.

26:02.395 --> 26:05.732
I never meant
for any of this to happen.

26:06.733 --> 26:08.902
But when Nadia grows up...

26:09.903 --> 26:12.614
..and she finds out what you
really are, she will hate you.

26:14.241 --> 26:16.660
Last chance, Peter.

26:17.869 --> 26:21.539
(SNIFFLES) Give me my kid back

26:21.706 --> 26:24.584
or I'm gonna come after you
with all I got.

26:27.754 --> 26:30.757
Come the next full moon,
there will be blood.

26:31.883 --> 26:35.095
I'm gonna rip out
your fucking heart.

26:36.680 --> 26:38.598
Yeah.

26:41.476 --> 26:43.478
(PHONE BEEPS)

26:45.855 --> 26:47.565
(PHONE BEEPS)

26:57.951 --> 27:00.161
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

27:05.917 --> 27:08.086
You have company.

27:09.963 --> 27:13.258
- May we come in?
- Of course.

27:13.425 --> 27:16.636
SHELLEY: This
is a nice surprise.

27:16.803 --> 27:18.847
Who is the little one?

27:19.014 --> 27:22.475
Nadia. She's your niece.

27:23.476 --> 27:25.437
My niece?

27:25.603 --> 27:27.564
- (BURBLES)
- SHELLEY: You didn't mention...

27:29.649 --> 27:32.444
What happened? It looks like
there was a war downstairs.

27:32.610 --> 27:36.781
Police invasion. Apparently,
it's a crime to be homeless.

27:36.948 --> 27:38.700
And where did everybody go?

27:38.867 --> 27:41.119
Somewhere else.

27:41.286 --> 27:43.788
Did you come to keep
Aunt Shelley company?

27:43.955 --> 27:46.708
Little kids usually scream
and run the other way

27:46.875 --> 27:48.626
when they see me coming.

27:48.793 --> 27:51.087
She knows you're family.

27:51.254 --> 27:54.341
- How?
- She just knows.

27:55.342 --> 27:57.969
Lucky for her,
there's no family resemblance.

27:58.136 --> 28:00.388
ANNIE: Um... Listen.
I need a favour.

28:00.555 --> 28:02.098
Sure.

28:02.265 --> 28:05.852
Could you watch Nadia
for an hour or so?

28:09.773 --> 28:12.233
ROMAN: Apologies for
the close quarters.

28:12.400 --> 28:14.819
The boardroom is still a work
in progress after the shoot-out.

28:14.986 --> 28:16.905
Regarding that matter,
there's going to be

28:17.072 --> 28:18.823
an incident report
on your desk Monday morning.

28:18.990 --> 28:20.909
I don't have to read
a report. I was there.

28:21.076 --> 28:23.661
What I need is for you to make
sure it doesn't happen again.

28:23.828 --> 28:26.289
We've also reviewed our
protocols after Pryce's murder.

28:26.456 --> 28:28.541
The assailant was unarmed
and cleared security...

28:28.708 --> 28:30.210
Save it.

28:30.377 --> 28:32.629
We have an urgent matter
that needs your full attention.

28:34.547 --> 28:37.133
This is Nadia - the work
product of Pryce's research

28:37.300 --> 28:41.262
into extra-uterine life,
the first marketable prototype.

28:41.429 --> 28:44.474
She was stolen from
our facility by this woman

28:44.641 --> 28:46.267
who orchestrated Pryce's murder

28:46.434 --> 28:48.478
as a diversionary tactic
to make the grab.

28:48.645 --> 28:51.022
We were not aware
this prototype was on-site.

28:51.189 --> 28:52.732
You don't have the clearance.

28:52.899 --> 28:55.402
She goes by the name of Annie
Archambeau - probably an alias.

28:55.568 --> 28:57.320
She's an international
intelligence operative

28:57.487 --> 28:59.114
up for auction.

28:59.280 --> 29:01.116
Find the kid
and terminate the operative.

29:01.282 --> 29:02.784
What you're asking us
to do, sir,

29:02.951 --> 29:04.661
doesn't really fit
our job description.

29:04.828 --> 29:07.330
We're responsible for building
security, not something like...

29:07.497 --> 29:09.874
Do I look like a complete
fucking idiot to you?

29:10.041 --> 29:11.835
No, sir.

29:12.001 --> 29:14.045
I must look like one
because you seem to think

29:14.212 --> 29:16.881
I don't have the faintest
fucking idea who I'm talking to.

29:17.048 --> 29:19.217
Most of you were recruited
out of black ops

29:19.384 --> 29:23.054
to be Pryce's personal, highly
paid mischief and mayhem crew.

29:23.221 --> 29:26.599
But you're working for me now
and you have your assignments.

29:27.600 --> 29:30.603
(TAPS SCREEN) OK?

29:31.896 --> 29:34.524
Now please leave me
the fuck alone.

29:51.958 --> 29:53.793
Oh, it's unlocked.

29:57.297 --> 30:01.134
Oh, there you are.
Come in. Come in.

30:07.223 --> 30:08.933
I got your messages.

30:09.100 --> 30:11.603
OLIVIA: Oh, I was afraid
you'd forgotten about us.

30:11.769 --> 30:13.855
We're so happy you're here.

30:14.022 --> 30:16.649
Happy? Baby,
we're fucking ecstatic.

30:16.816 --> 30:19.694
- I just came in my pants.
- Go away.

30:19.861 --> 30:23.740
Um...you said
you're not feeling well.

30:24.782 --> 30:28.536
I picked up whatever's
going around. I'll be fine.

30:30.580 --> 30:32.957
I've been meaning to come by.

30:33.124 --> 30:35.418
There's something
I've been wanting to ask...

30:35.585 --> 30:38.588
I really do have to apologise
for our last visit.

30:38.755 --> 30:42.133
I was so mad at Norman
for fucking you.

30:42.300 --> 30:45.762
- Norman?
- Roman, your brother.

30:45.929 --> 30:49.224
I was so busy pissing acid
on that little shit,

30:49.390 --> 30:51.476
I didn't give a moment's
thought to the fact

30:51.643 --> 30:55.104
that you're probably terribly
uncomfortable with the whole...

30:55.271 --> 30:56.940
Whatever it was.

30:57.106 --> 30:59.067
She means she's sorry.

31:01.194 --> 31:03.238
That's OK.

31:04.239 --> 31:07.033
The first time I came here,
I lied to you.

31:08.034 --> 31:10.787
- I never met Dimitri.
- Oh, snap! Here we go.

31:10.954 --> 31:12.997
Lucky you.

31:13.164 --> 31:16.167
I said that because I wanted
to see how you'd react.

31:17.710 --> 31:19.504
Did I pass?

31:19.671 --> 31:21.798
When I was old enough
to travel on my own,

31:21.965 --> 31:23.675
I went looking for him.

31:24.676 --> 31:27.595
He'd been killed
some years before.

31:28.596 --> 31:31.724
They found his body
in the village square.

31:31.891 --> 31:35.979
Things had been done to him,
mutilation and such.

31:36.145 --> 31:38.606
Oh, such an idyllic place,

31:38.773 --> 31:41.317
the old country,
from the outside,

31:41.484 --> 31:44.612
but underneath...oof!

31:44.779 --> 31:46.406
I remember you telling me

31:46.573 --> 31:49.075
how you'd been planning
to run off together.

31:49.242 --> 31:52.662
He went to the next village
to steal a horse

31:52.829 --> 31:54.664
and you never
heard from him again.

31:54.831 --> 31:56.708
Well, I guess now we know why.

31:56.874 --> 32:00.003
He'd been mutilated and
left in the centre of town.

32:00.169 --> 32:02.171
Everyone knew about it.

32:04.173 --> 32:06.509
Oh, it was just so long ago.

32:06.676 --> 32:10.471
You were carrying his child,
your lover disappears.

32:10.638 --> 32:14.559
They find a boy the same age,
body parts all over the place.

32:14.726 --> 32:16.561
You didn't put it together?

32:16.728 --> 32:19.022
What's your point?

32:19.188 --> 32:22.358
"Men leave.
That's what they do."

32:22.525 --> 32:24.360
Isn't that what you told me?

32:28.406 --> 32:30.325
I don't think men leave you.

32:30.491 --> 32:32.910
I think you prey on them.

32:33.911 --> 32:38.625
Men are a cheap and easy
source of protein

32:38.791 --> 32:40.835
and they do leave.

32:41.002 --> 32:43.421
When I found out that's
what Dimitri was planning,

32:43.588 --> 32:47.216
I certainly wasn't gonna let him
do that to my unborn child.

32:47.383 --> 32:49.427
(SCOFFS)

32:49.594 --> 32:51.971
You're nothing
if not selfless, Olivia.

32:52.138 --> 32:56.100
In retrospect, I'm certain
I did us both a favour.

32:58.436 --> 33:00.480
Oh, um...

33:02.106 --> 33:07.862
I...I've really enjoyed our
time together, however brief,

33:08.029 --> 33:14.535
but, with regret, I must
do what needs to be done.

33:16.329 --> 33:18.623
Ugh!

33:18.790 --> 33:20.958
(ANNIE GROANS)

33:57.286 --> 34:00.248
(EXHALES) Good to be home.

34:05.753 --> 34:08.755
(INHALES AND EXHALES DEEPLY)

34:11.592 --> 34:13.428
Ooh!

34:17.889 --> 34:20.685
ROMAN: You know what
I like about this place?

34:21.978 --> 34:23.896
WOMAN: It's spacious?

34:26.983 --> 34:29.025
It's mine.

34:33.947 --> 34:36.074
(NADIA BURBLES)

34:38.870 --> 34:44.000
(READS) "Remove diaper
from wrapping. Unvelcro tabs."

34:47.670 --> 34:50.547
- Um...
- (NADIA BABBLES)

35:01.809 --> 35:06.147
AITOR: The Inuit put layers
of moss tucked inside sealskin.

35:07.148 --> 35:09.066
They created the most
technologically advanced

35:09.233 --> 35:10.860
diaper of its day.

35:11.027 --> 35:14.739
It was both absorbent
and waterproof.

35:17.700 --> 35:22.079
I see you got yourself a baby
since I saw you last.

35:22.246 --> 35:24.624
Things happen fast around here.

35:24.791 --> 35:26.501
Who is that little person?

35:26.667 --> 35:28.252
Her name is Nadia.

35:28.419 --> 35:32.131
- Nadia?
- My niece.

35:33.800 --> 35:35.551
Back in Elizabethan times,

35:35.718 --> 35:38.471
they didn't change diapers
but once a week.

35:38.638 --> 35:40.431
I often wondered if that's what

35:40.598 --> 35:42.558
kicked off the age
of exploration -

35:42.725 --> 35:45.102
travelling across oceans
to distant lands

35:45.269 --> 35:48.105
to escape the aroma
of young families -

35:48.272 --> 35:49.899
because the history
of toileting's pretty much

35:50.066 --> 35:52.318
the history of everything
when you get right down to it.

35:52.485 --> 35:55.238
For a smart guy who knows
a whole lot about a whole lot,

35:55.404 --> 35:57.073
you're pretty dumb sometimes.

35:59.200 --> 36:02.829
I reached that same conclusion
around Bald Knob, Arkansas.

36:05.665 --> 36:07.500
So you're aware
that it seems to be easier

36:07.667 --> 36:09.710
for you to stand up
in front of 100 people

36:09.877 --> 36:12.296
and open a vein
than it is to talk to me?

36:14.674 --> 36:16.467
I am aware.

36:17.718 --> 36:19.679
And it occurred to me

36:19.846 --> 36:22.306
that telling the truth
to entertain an audience

36:22.473 --> 36:24.517
isn't anywhere near the same

36:24.684 --> 36:27.311
as telling the truth
'cause it's the truth.

36:27.478 --> 36:29.730
It's probably
a good deal less honest.

36:29.897 --> 36:31.858
That is my strong sense.

36:35.194 --> 36:38.322
So is there anything I should
know or that you want to tell me

36:38.489 --> 36:41.576
or do I need to go round up
a few dozen more people?

36:43.536 --> 36:46.664
No. No, that's it.

36:50.459 --> 36:54.130
You know everything about me.
You've seen me at my worst.

36:56.716 --> 37:00.177
Before I have to leave
to explore distant lands,

37:00.344 --> 37:03.806
we gotta figure out how
to change this baby's diaper.

37:03.973 --> 37:06.350
Let me show you.

37:06.517 --> 37:08.436
It's very simple.

37:09.604 --> 37:13.524
Stretchy part goes in the back.
This goes in the front.

37:13.691 --> 37:15.610
Connect the tabs.

37:15.776 --> 37:17.945
- Connect the tabs.
- Mm-hm.

37:18.112 --> 37:21.365
MAN: Ma'am,
this is a secure floor.

37:21.532 --> 37:25.202
And this is a Godfrey family
member who's fallen gravely ill.

37:25.369 --> 37:26.996
Dr Pryce is expecting us.

37:27.163 --> 37:30.750
Ma'am, Dr Pryce is dead.

37:30.917 --> 37:32.793
Well, I'll speak
to Dr Blinsky, then.

37:32.960 --> 37:35.463
Ms Godfrey, you need
to step out of the elevator.

37:35.630 --> 37:37.715
Please.

37:38.716 --> 37:41.928
- Ms Godfrey...
- Bip, bip, bip!

37:42.094 --> 37:43.930
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

38:00.821 --> 38:03.991
(STAMMERS) You just
killed that guard!

38:04.158 --> 38:06.911
Time for you to do
that consciousness

38:07.078 --> 38:09.622
transfer la-di-da
you do so well.

38:11.791 --> 38:13.459
BLINSKY: Who is she?

38:13.626 --> 38:15.294
The perfect fit,

38:15.461 --> 38:17.630
though I never imagined
myself as a size two.

38:17.797 --> 38:19.423
I'd throw a hump into that.

38:19.590 --> 38:21.175
Are you crazy?

38:21.342 --> 38:23.928
Fucking bat-shit meshuga,

38:24.095 --> 38:27.807
as my African demigod associate
can certainly vouch for.

38:27.974 --> 38:31.394
(SPEAKS SPANISH)

38:31.560 --> 38:33.229
Ooh, and he gives good head.

38:33.396 --> 38:37.400
Mrs Godfrey,
you are obviously extremely ill.

38:37.566 --> 38:39.485
See, he's not buying
the green tea or borax either.

38:39.652 --> 38:42.238
You won't be able
to walk out of here.

38:42.405 --> 38:44.865
There will be an army of cops
looking for you.

38:45.032 --> 38:47.702
No, no, no. I'm not
walking out of here. She is.

38:47.868 --> 38:52.790
My crimes will die with me,
but I did not shoot the deputy.

38:52.957 --> 38:54.458
I'm not doing this.

38:54.625 --> 38:58.170
You are not of sound mind
or body and this...

38:58.337 --> 39:00.840
..this person is being coerced.

39:01.007 --> 39:04.051
- (ANNIE GROANS)
- Dr Blinsky.

39:05.052 --> 39:08.139
This is best for all concerned.

39:08.305 --> 39:11.350
Annie will get to be
with her departed family

39:11.517 --> 39:13.477
at Six Flags over Jesus,

39:13.644 --> 39:16.981
I will be the very best
size two I can be

39:17.148 --> 39:19.150
and you will have
the satisfaction

39:19.316 --> 39:21.318
of restoring everyone
to wholeness.

39:21.485 --> 39:24.155
I mean, isn't that
what doctors do after all?

39:24.321 --> 39:26.115
You'll have to kill me first.

39:29.368 --> 39:31.829
I thought you'd say
something annoying like that.

39:31.996 --> 39:34.999
That would leave little
Auden Blinsky without her daddy.

39:35.166 --> 39:37.001
Pretentious name, by the way.

39:37.168 --> 39:38.711
No, no.

39:38.878 --> 39:42.048
Her dance class at the community
centre lets out in...

39:42.214 --> 39:44.300
..ooh, one hour.

39:44.467 --> 39:48.137
Poor little thing is gonna
miss Christmas. Oh, well.

39:48.304 --> 39:50.848
Don't even...don't even
talk like that. You wouldn't.

39:51.015 --> 39:52.975
Oh, the girls look so cute

39:53.142 --> 39:54.769
getting ready
for spring recital.

39:54.935 --> 39:58.898
Just do what she says.
You don't have a choice.

40:01.942 --> 40:03.861
Oh, my God...

40:04.028 --> 40:07.031
(BIRDS CHIRP)

40:35.601 --> 40:38.604
(SOLEMN MUSIC)

41:33.075 --> 41:35.452
I'm going to sedate you.
You won't feel a thing.

41:35.619 --> 41:37.246
Isn't this the way it should be,

41:37.413 --> 41:40.624
children being sacrificed
for their parent?

41:40.791 --> 41:43.752
CHANGO: I'm pretty sure
it's the other way around.

41:45.754 --> 41:47.464
Look straight ahead.

41:48.465 --> 41:49.967
(WHISPERS)
I'm going to unlock you.

41:50.134 --> 41:52.136
Run to the module.
I'll be right behind you.

41:52.303 --> 41:54.346
We'll lock ourselves in.

41:57.266 --> 42:00.519
I'm gonna do a quick
neurological exam.

42:00.686 --> 42:02.771
Pryce never did
anything like that.

42:02.938 --> 42:05.983
Yeah, well, Pryce...
Pryce is dead.

42:06.150 --> 42:07.776
- (TUNING FORK RINGS)
- Did I know that?

42:07.943 --> 42:10.446
- I think you did.
- Well, hurry up.

42:10.613 --> 42:14.325
I feel death's clammy fingers
wrapping around my mortal coil.

42:14.491 --> 42:16.660
Tell me when you can't
hear this anymore.

42:16.827 --> 42:19.705
(RINGING CONTINUES)

42:26.921 --> 42:29.006
Key West this,
Key West that...

42:29.173 --> 42:32.134
A town full of drunks
getting skin cancer.

42:32.301 --> 42:34.011
I knew Hemingway personally -

42:34.178 --> 42:37.973
dull as dirt until
Papa got six daiquiris in him.

42:38.140 --> 42:39.725
Not great shakes in the sack -

42:39.892 --> 42:42.770
short and clipped,
like his sentences.

42:42.937 --> 42:44.688
I thought the cats
were a cute touch.

42:44.855 --> 42:47.608
He would have made
a great Santa Claus.

42:47.775 --> 42:49.360
Ohh...

42:49.526 --> 42:52.321
(COUNTS SILENTLY)

42:54.657 --> 42:57.159
Ugh! (GRUNTS)

42:57.326 --> 42:59.578
What is it with you and
putting people in this thing?

42:59.745 --> 43:01.205
- Open it up.
- I can't!

43:01.372 --> 43:04.083
Open it up or I'll use
your spine to pry it open.

43:04.250 --> 43:07.503
OK, OK! I programmed
a manual override.

43:07.670 --> 43:09.964
Ohh...

43:13.842 --> 43:16.720
- I am so sorry. I tried.
- Bip!

43:16.887 --> 43:18.889
Just a minute.

43:22.351 --> 43:24.311
(MOUTHS WORDS)

43:28.482 --> 43:31.402
(AIR HISSES)

43:32.653 --> 43:35.656
- What is she doing?
- I don't know.

43:35.823 --> 43:37.700
- Open the fucking door!
- I'm trying to!

43:37.866 --> 43:40.035
It's hard to type
with blood on my hands!

43:40.202 --> 43:41.912
OLIVIA: Open
the fucking door now!

43:43.414 --> 43:45.749
OLIVIA: What are you doing?

43:48.919 --> 43:55.718
My prayer was that you know
faith and the love of God.

43:55.884 --> 43:57.594
No matter.

43:57.761 --> 44:01.473
The grace of the Lord
will find you

44:01.640 --> 44:05.853
and transform you
into everything you're not -

44:06.020 --> 44:11.025
perfect, whole and complete.

44:13.819 --> 44:15.529
Adieu, Maman.

44:23.287 --> 44:25.914
(OLIVIA GASPS) Open it up!

44:27.833 --> 44:31.837
Open it up! No! No!

44:32.004 --> 44:34.089
(SCREAMS)

44:34.256 --> 44:38.510
No! No! No!

44:43.057 --> 44:44.808
No!

44:44.975 --> 44:46.852
(SCREAMING FADES)

44:48.854 --> 44:50.397
What are you reading?

44:50.564 --> 44:52.566
Your reviews.

44:53.567 --> 44:55.194
(SIGHS) How much
do they hate me?

44:55.361 --> 44:58.447
Hate you?
They adore you.

44:59.448 --> 45:01.283
But I couldn't
remember my lines.

45:01.450 --> 45:03.160
Oh, well, people are
always more forgiving

45:03.327 --> 45:04.953
than you ever
give them credit for.

45:05.120 --> 45:09.041
"A performance worthy
of a young Julie Christie."

45:09.208 --> 45:12.878
I don't know who that is,
but they seem to love her.

45:13.045 --> 45:15.297
"Brilliant." "Iconic."

45:15.464 --> 45:18.092
"First Lady
of the London stage."

45:18.258 --> 45:21.011
"A tour de force."
What are you so worried about?

45:21.178 --> 45:24.181
You're a star. It says so
right there in black and white.

45:24.348 --> 45:26.058
It feels like
I don't deserve it.

45:26.225 --> 45:30.687
Oh, well, it's not up to you
to decide. That's for them.

45:32.731 --> 45:34.733
You know what your problem is?

45:34.900 --> 45:36.652
You are self-centred.

45:36.819 --> 45:38.695
I've been told that before.

45:38.862 --> 45:40.781
You don't know how
to let yourself be loved

45:40.948 --> 45:42.574
because it's out
of your control.

45:42.741 --> 45:45.119
Being loved isn't
even about you.

45:45.285 --> 45:46.912
That's where your problem is.

45:47.079 --> 45:49.289
But it makes no sense.

45:49.456 --> 45:52.459
You have to train yourself
to drink in their adoration

45:52.626 --> 45:54.878
and be grateful for it.

45:55.045 --> 45:56.672
Law of attraction.

45:56.839 --> 46:01.093
The love you make
is equal to...whatever.

46:01.260 --> 46:04.555
Here. Let me show you.

46:09.601 --> 46:13.522
She is the lady and the tiger,

46:13.689 --> 46:17.776
darkness at noon,
the lurch you got left in.

46:17.943 --> 46:20.654
May I present
the only woman I know

46:20.821 --> 46:25.492
who wears my heart on
her sleeve, Olivia Godfrey.

46:25.659 --> 46:28.662
(WILD CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

46:51.685 --> 46:55.689
Oh! Thank you. Thank you.

46:55.856 --> 46:58.859
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE
CONTINUE)

47:07.910 --> 47:11.914
OLIVIA: Thank you.
I...I love you all.

47:13.624 --> 47:15.334
Thank you all.

47:15.501 --> 47:17.753
(ALARM BLARES DISTANTLY)

47:17.920 --> 47:20.255
Bip...

47:20.422 --> 47:22.925
..bip...

47:23.091 --> 47:25.010
..bip.

47:36.522 --> 47:40.359
Thank you all.

47:42.236 --> 47:44.988
What do you mean you're leaving?

47:45.155 --> 47:47.199
(ALARM CONTINUES)

47:48.408 --> 47:50.869
Bip...

47:51.036 --> 47:53.539
..bip...

47:54.957 --> 47:58.293
Thank you all

47:58.460 --> 48:03.924
and to all, a good night.

48:27.447 --> 48:30.450
(CLOCK TICKS)

48:38.542 --> 48:41.545
(GUNSHOTS)

48:48.010 --> 48:50.262
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

48:57.227 --> 48:59.396
That gun's not gonna
do you much good.

49:02.441 --> 49:04.818
PETER: Yeah.

49:07.112 --> 49:10.198
Arggh...!

49:10.365 --> 49:12.409
(ROARS)

49:23.003 --> 49:24.838
(SNARLS AND ROARS)

49:30.844 --> 49:33.430
DESTINY'S VOICE: Roman...

49:39.186 --> 49:42.022
- (SNARLS)
- Ohh!

49:42.189 --> 49:45.150
- (PETER YELPS)
- (GRUNTS)

49:47.235 --> 49:50.447
- (GROWLS LOWLY)
- (COUGHS)

49:52.866 --> 49:55.869
(WHEEZES)

49:57.537 --> 49:59.748
Oh, I...

50:00.749 --> 50:03.043
..I can't move.

50:06.129 --> 50:07.756
My body's broken.

50:07.923 --> 50:09.675
(GROWLS)

50:09.841 --> 50:11.593
ROMAN: Look at me.

50:11.760 --> 50:13.303
Just do it.

50:13.470 --> 50:15.305
Please.

50:17.683 --> 50:19.393
I don't want to be this.

50:20.477 --> 50:22.145
Look at you.

50:22.312 --> 50:25.440
You're gonna live out your days
as a fucking animal.

50:27.442 --> 50:31.029
(WEEPS) It's over, man.

50:35.450 --> 50:37.828
It's over, man.

50:38.829 --> 50:42.916
- (SOBS)
- (SNARLS)

50:43.917 --> 50:47.045
Just do it! Just do it.

50:48.547 --> 50:50.882
(SNARLS)

50:57.723 --> 50:59.516
(GAGS)

51:08.859 --> 51:10.527
MAN ON RADIO:
<i>Alright, our next caller</i>

51:10.694 --> 51:12.362
<i>is Vlad Wojack
of Hemlock Grove.</i>

51:12.529 --> 51:14.197
<i>What's on your mind, Vlad?</i>

51:14.364 --> 51:16.324
VLAD: <i>We need to look
at these unexplained deaths</i>

51:16.491 --> 51:18.827
<i>and disappearances through
the prism of rational thought.</i>

51:18.994 --> 51:22.372
<i>Blaming them on made-up stuff
like vampires and lycanthropes</i>

51:22.539 --> 51:24.875
<i>trivialises
what's really going on here.</i>

51:25.041 --> 51:28.545
<i>The real cause of all
this suffering? EBEs.</i>

51:28.712 --> 51:31.256
MAN: <i>Extra-biological
entities? Aliens?</i>

51:31.423 --> 51:33.091
VLAD: <i>Couldn't be more obvious.</i>

51:33.258 --> 51:34.760
SHELLEY: Ever been to Montana?

51:34.926 --> 51:36.762
AITOR: Nope.

51:36.928 --> 51:39.389
They got sky for
the taking, I'm told.

51:39.556 --> 51:43.018
Well, let's go get us some sky.

51:43.185 --> 51:44.936
You given any more thought

51:45.103 --> 51:47.230
about what to do
with that bag of money?

51:47.397 --> 51:49.357
Yeah.

51:49.524 --> 51:51.276
Nothing.

51:51.443 --> 51:55.238
We're a couple of poets.
What do we know about money?

51:55.405 --> 51:58.074
We'll wait till Nadia grows up.

51:58.241 --> 52:00.368
She'll know what to do with it.

52:01.620 --> 52:03.955
Look!

52:04.122 --> 52:06.082
What?

52:07.417 --> 52:09.085
Never mind.

52:11.421 --> 52:14.007
It was nothing.

